.TH PKM 1 "2026-04-21" "pkm 0.1.0" "InterGenOS System Administration"
.SH NAME
pkm \- InterGenOS package manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pkm
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-\-db\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.I command
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pkm
is the InterGenOS package manager. It installs, removes, queries, and
verifies packages built from InterGenOS's tiered source tree. Packages
are distributed as
.B .igos.tar.gz
archives with accompanying metadata and are tracked in a local SQLite
database at
.IR /var/lib/igos/pkm.db .
.PP
Repository configuration lives in
.IR /etc/pkm/repos.conf .
The default shipped repository is the official InterGenOS mirror. GPG
verification becomes available once the signing-key ceremony completes;
until then the trust model is TLS + repository-URL pinning.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR install " \fIPACKAGE\fR [\fIPACKAGE...\fR] [\fB\-\-archive\fR \fIPATH\fR]"
Install one or more packages. If no local archive is supplied, packages
are fetched from configured repositories and dependencies are resolved
automatically.
.TP
.BR install-helper " \fIPACKAGE\fR"
Install proprietary or third-party software via a named download helper
(for example,
.BR chrome ,
.BR vscode ,
.BR claude-code ).
Helpers are installed at
.IR /usr/bin/igos-install-* .
This exists so the user-facing interface is one command regardless of
whether a package is source-built or vendor-supplied.
.TP
.BR remove " \fIPACKAGE\fR [\fB\-\-force\fR]"
Remove an installed package.
.B \-\-force
permits removal even when other packages still depend on it.
.TP
.BR list " [" installed | available | upgradable "] [" \-\-tier " \fITIER\fR]"
List packages. The default view is
.BR installed .
Restrict to a tier with
.B \-\-tier
.RI ( toolchain ,
.IR core ,
.IR base ,
.IR desktop ,
.IR extra ,
.IR ai ).
.TP
.B update
Sync package indexes from every enabled repository.
.TP
.BR upgrade " [\fIPACKAGE...\fR]"
Upgrade installed packages to the latest versions available in the
configured repositories. With no arguments, every installed package is
considered.
.TP
.BR search " \fITERM\fR"
Search local and remote indexes for packages matching
.IR TERM .
Installed matches are labelled inline.
.TP
.BR info " \fIPACKAGE\fR"
Show package details: version, tier, description, license, build and
install dates, install method, dependencies, and reverse dependencies.
.TP
.BR files " \fIPACKAGE\fR"
List files owned by an installed package.
.TP
.BR provides " \fIFILE\fR"
Report which installed package owns a given file.
.TP
.BR verify " [\fIPACKAGE\fR] [\fB\-\-all\fR]"
Verify package integrity against recorded file hashes. With
.B \-\-all
every installed package is verified and a summary is printed.
.TP
.BR depends " \fIPACKAGE\fR [\fB\-\-reverse\fR]"
Show the dependencies of a package. With
.B \-\-reverse
show which installed packages depend on it.
.TP
.BR history " [\fIPACKAGE\fR]"
Show operation history (install/remove/upgrade). An optional
.I PACKAGE
argument filters to a single package.
.TP
.B import
Import pre-existing text-manifest records into the SQLite database.
Used when migrating from the legacy pkm text-manifest format.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-db " \fIPATH\fR"
Override the default database path
.RI ( /var/lib/igos/pkm.db ).
Primarily useful in tests and rescue scenarios.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/pkm/repos.conf
Repository configuration. Each stanza defines a named repository with a
base URL and optional trust settings.
.TP
.I /var/lib/igos/pkm.db
SQLite database tracking installed packages, files, and history. Self-
initialises on first invocation.
.TP
.I /var/lib/igos/packages/
Per-package metadata directories.
.TP
.I /var/lib/igos/archives/
Cached
.B .igos.tar.gz
archives.
.SH EXAMPLES
Install a single package from the default repository:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm install htop
.RE
.PP
Install several packages in one operation; dependencies resolve
automatically:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm install vim tmux ripgrep
.RE
.PP
Install from a local archive when offline:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm install vim \-\-archive /path/to/vim-9.1.1.igos.tar.gz
.RE
.PP
Install proprietary software via a download helper:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm install-helper vscode
.RE
.PP
Show what a package installed, along with its version and tier:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm info htop
.RE
.PP
List every file owned by a package:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm files htop
.RE
.PP
Find the owning package for a file on disk:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm provides /usr/bin/nano
.RE
.PP
Verify the integrity of every installed package:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm verify \-\-all
.RE
.PP
List everything in the desktop tier:
.PP
.RS
.B pkm list installed \-\-tier desktop
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
